---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import LegalNav from '../components/LegalNav.astro'
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro'

const EFFECTIVE_DATE = 'March 1, 2026'
const CONTACT_EMAIL = 'privacy@absoluteear.com'
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Absolute Ear"
  description="Privacy policy for the Absolute Ear app."
>
  <LegalNav pageTitle="Privacy Policy" />

  <!-- ── CONTENT ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <main id="main-content" style="background:#f7f7f5; min-height:100dvh;">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-24">

      <p style="font-size:13px; color:#8d96a5; font-family:var(--font-mono); margin-bottom:1rem;">
        Effective {EFFECTIVE_DATE}
      </p>
      <h1 style="font-size:clamp(2rem,5vw,3rem); font-weight:700; letter-spacing:-0.03em; color:#0f1115; line-height:1.1; margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Absolute Ear is an ear training app that helps you develop reliable pitch recognition through
        progressive, focused practice. This policy explains what information we collect, how we use
        it, and your choices. We keep things short and plain.
      </p>

      <hr class="divider" />

      <section>
        <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          Absolute Ear is operated by an independent developer. If you have privacy questions,
          email us at <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. What we collect</h2>

        <h3>If you use the app as a guest</h3>
        <p>
          You can use Absolute Ear without creating an account. In guest mode we do not collect
          your name, email address, or any other personally identifiable information. Your practice
          progress is stored only on your device.
        </p>

        <h3>If you create an account</h3>
        <p>We collect the following depending on the sign-in method you choose:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Sign in with Apple</strong> — Apple shares your name and either your real
            email address or an anonymized relay address, depending on the privacy setting you
            choose in the Apple sign-in prompt.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Sign in with Google</strong> — Google shares your name and email address.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Email (one-time code)</strong> — We receive the email address you enter to
            send your sign-in code.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Once signed in, we store your account information and practice data (session history,
          accuracy scores, streaks, badges, and progress through modules) on our backend, which is
          powered by <strong>Convex</strong> (convex.dev).
        </p>

        <h3>Subscription data</h3>
        <p>
          Subscriptions are processed entirely through the Apple App Store and Google Play. We
          receive a confirmation of your subscription status but never see or store your payment
          card details.
        </p>

        <h3>Crash and error data</h3>
        <p>
          We use <strong>Sentry</strong> (sentry.io) to capture crash reports and error logs. Crash
          reporting is always on and cannot be disabled. When a crash occurs, Sentry automatically
          collects technical information such as the device type, operating system version, app
          version, and a stack trace. This data does not include your name or email address, but
          may include a randomly generated device identifier assigned by Sentry.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. How we use your information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To operate your account and sync your practice progress across devices.</li>
          <li>To deliver and manage your subscription.</li>
          <li>To diagnose and fix crashes and bugs.</li>
          <li>To respond to support or privacy requests you send us.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not sell your data. We do not use your data for advertising. We do not build
          behavioral profiles or share data with ad networks.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Third-party services</h2>
        <p>
          The following services may receive some of the data described above. Each has its own
          privacy policy.
        </p>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Service</th>
              <th>Purpose</th>
              <th>Data shared</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Convex</td>
              <td>Backend and database</td>
              <td>Account info, practice data</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Sentry</td>
              <td>Crash reporting</td>
              <td>Device info, error logs</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Apple</td>
              <td>Sign-in, payments</td>
              <td>Name, email (if Apple sign-in), subscription status</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Google</td>
              <td>Sign-in</td>
              <td>Name, email (if Google sign-in)</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Children's privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Absolute Ear does not target children under 13, but we recognize that younger users may
          use the app under parental supervision. We do not knowingly collect personal information
          from children under 13.
        </p>
        <p>
          Because a full guest mode is available — requiring no account and no personal data — young
          learners can practice freely without providing any information to us. If a child creates
          an account, the account holds only an email address and practice scores.
        </p>
        <p>
          The app contains no advertising, no social features, and no violent or mature content.
          It is suitable for all ages.
        </p>
        <p>
        If you believe we have inadvertently received personal information from a child under 13,
          please contact us at <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a> and we will
          delete it promptly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Data retention</h2>
        <p>
          We keep your account data for as long as your account exists. Crash and error data is
          retained according to Sentry's default retention policy (90 days for free plans).
          When you delete your account, your personal data and practice history are deleted
          immediately from your device and our backend database.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Your rights and choices</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Access or correction</strong> — Email us and we will tell you what data we hold
            for your account and correct any inaccuracies.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Deletion</strong> — You can delete your account directly in the app. This
            immediately and permanently removes your personal data and practice history from your
            device and our backend database. You can also request deletion by emailing
            <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Depending on where you live, you may have additional rights under laws such as the GDPR
          (European Union) or CCPA (California). We honor those rights. Email us to exercise them.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Security</h2>
        <p>
          Your data is transmitted over HTTPS and stored on Convex's infrastructure, which uses
          industry-standard security practices. No method of transmission or storage is 100%
          secure, but we take reasonable steps to protect your information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          If we make material changes, we will update the effective date at the top of this page.
          For significant changes we will notify account holders by email. Continued use of the app
          after changes are posted constitutes acceptance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>10. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions, requests, or concerns about this policy:
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <SiteFooter activePage="privacy" />
</Layout>

<style>
  .lead {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #3d4451;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .divider {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid #e2e4e8;
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.1875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: #0f1115;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #0f1115;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #3d4451;
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #3d4451;
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }

  a {
    color: #0e9aa7;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  th {
    text-align: left;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #0f1115;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #e2e4e8;
  }

  td {
    color: #3d4451;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e2e4e8;
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  tr:last-child td {
    border-bottom: none;
  }
</style>
